                            "wrapper": {
                                "width": "",
                                "class": "",
                                "id": ""
                            },
                            "default_value": "<p>The Tripoint of Russia, Finland, and Norway is one of the most remote and symbolically charged border crossings in Europe. Known locally as Treriksrøysa (Norwegian), Kolmen valtakunnan rajapyykki (Finnish), and Трёхгранка (Russian), it’s where the territories of these three very different nations converge in a lonely bogland in the far north—deep in the Arctic wilderness, above 69°N. You can hike to the tripoint from the Finnish side, pushing your bike for large parts of the 15km.<\/p>",
                            "allow_in_bindings": 0,
                            "tabs": "all",
                            "toolbar": "full",
